# phaser-settings library contract

- **phaser-settings is a library**: Only the public API from the package entrypoint may be used by consuming apps. Do not import from internal paths (e.g. `phaser-settings/validation` or `phaser-settings/ui/...`). Use only `import … from 'phaser-settings'`. The public surface is defined in [src/index.ts](src/index.ts) and [PUBLIC_API.md](PUBLIC_API.md).

- **When editing this repo**: Do not change integration semantics (lifecycle, singleton, validation, coercion) without updating docs ([docs/INTEGRATION.md](docs/INTEGRATION.md), [docs/API.md](docs/API.md)) and tests.

- **When editing app code that uses phaser-settings**: Do not add wrappers or app-local logic that replace or duplicate the package’s resolution/validation. Use the package’s extension points (see [docs/INTEGRATION.md](docs/INTEGRATION.md)) or propose an API change in the shared package.

See [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) and [docs/INTEGRATION.md](docs/INTEGRATION.md) for full rules and anti-goals.
